023package com.restfb.types.send;
024
025import com.restfb.Facebook;
026import com.restfb.types.AbstractFacebookType;
027
028/**
029 * Represents the
030 * <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/send-api-reference/quick-replies">Quick Reply</a>
031 */
032public class QuickReply extends AbstractFacebookType {
033  @Facebook("content_type")
034  private String contentType;
035  @Facebook
036  private String title;
037  @Facebook
038  private String payload;
039  @Facebook("image_url")
040  private String imageUrl;
041
042  /**
043   * @deprecated use constructor without contenttype instead. If using content type 'text' use
044   *             {@link QuickReply#QuickReply(String,String)} for 'location' use {@link QuickReply#QuickReply()}
045   */
046  @Deprecated
047  public QuickReply(String contentType, String title, String payload) {
048    this(title, payload);
049    this.contentType = contentType;
050  }
051
052  public QuickReply(String title, String payload) {
053    this.contentType = "text";
054    this.title = title;
055    this.payload = payload;
056  }
057
058  public QuickReply(QuickReplyType quickReplyType) {
059    this.contentType = quickReplyType.getContentType();
060  }
061
062
063  public enum QuickReplyType {
064    USER_EMAIL, USER_PHONE_NUMBER;
065
066    public String getContentType() {
067      return name().toLowerCase();
068    }
069  }
070

074  }

079  }

088    return this.imageUrl;
089  }
